						<summary>

						

						<p>On a stone set up near the well in the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1457, Pārttiva, Kārttika ba. 7, Thursday = Irregular.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records that Kṛishṇamarāju of •• tsarikoṇḍa dug out a well and conse crated the same in the temple of Kāḷēśvara, for the merit of his father Timmarāju and mother Veṁkaṁma. The donor is described as the servant of god Amarachaṇḍēśvara.</p>						

